Package <Unnamed>

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    BoardStyle
    The board style interface defines a strategy for creating a unique board style for the Mancala Board.
    MancalaModel
    The MancalaModel Interface describes some functionality that will be required of the Model used for Mancala by the Mancala User Interface classes.
    StoneLayout
    The stone layout interfaces describes a strategy for ordering a given amount of stones in an organized matter based on the amount of stones to be ordered, so that they can be drawn nicely inside of a pit.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    BlueSteel
    This is a board style that displays greyish blue colors with rounded rectangles for most elements, as well as displaying a 2.5d shadow for some elements.
    Jungle
    This is a board style that displays greenish colors for the board elements
    Date Created: 11/22/2012
    Date Updated: 11/22/2012
    MancalaBoardPanel
    The Mancala board panel is in charge of drawing the Mancala board, as well as all of it's contained pits.
    MancalaFrame
    The primary frame for the Mancala Game.
    MancalaPitPanel
    The mancala pit button is in charge of drawing the pit for the mancala board, as well as the correct number of stones inside of it.
    MancalaTest
    This is where main injection occurs, and loads up the MVC architecture.
    Model
    Fully working implementation of a model for mancala that implements MancalModel
    PitMancalaLayout
    The Mancala Pit Stone Layout is a stone layout for a Mancala Pit.
    PitNormalLayout
    The Normal Pit Stone Layout is a stone layout for a Normal Pit.
